(141, 1, '2024-07-10 13:08:26', '2024-07-10 13:08:26', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"toc1\">UI vs UX</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>UI and UX are the concepts that work parallelly</strong>&nbsp;to make a website, service, or any software product. UI (user interface) relates to the visual properties of a product, which includes the look, feel, design, and structure of all the elements to interact with.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Whereas UX (user experience) implies the behavioral properties of the UI</strong>&nbsp;and, more precisely, sets how a user can interact with your product and makes them feel them by using it.&nbsp;But they are depending upon each other. The absence of one of them will make the other useless.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Features of UI Design</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1. Visual Design:</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Typography:</strong> The choice of fonts and styles plays a crucial role in readability and brand identity. A UI designer selects fonts that are legible on various devices and ensures a consistent typographic hierarchy (headings, subheadings, body text) throughout the interface.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Color Schemes:</strong> Colors are chosen to create an aesthetically pleasing and functional interface. This includes primary colors for brand identity, secondary colors for accents, and ensuring sufficient contrast for readability and accessibility.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Icons and Imagery:</strong> Icons and images should be intuitive and support the content they accompany. Custom icons and high-quality images are often used to enhance the visual appeal and usability of the interface.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'Key Features of UI/UX Design', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '135-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-07-10 13:08:26', '2024-07-10 13:08:26', '', 135, 'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=141', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
